  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research evaluating CFD-based hemolysis prediction for centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The computational model targets absolute hemolysis index prediction for a Class III device at nominal operating points. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary conditions; sensitivity analyses confirm that shear-stress exposure time and blade tip clearance dominate output variance. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed by the assessment team; seven were formally scored and six were carried forward as epistemic gaps pending additional experimental data. The assessment team concluded that the model, as applied in ongoing clinical feasibility studies, meets the credibility threshold commensurate with the intended decision context. No structured Context of Use record has been filed under this Minimal-profile submission; the intended-use scope is described only in the narrative above.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-credibility",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
